00:23:31.930 --> 00:23:32.380 align:middle line:90%
and then--

00:23:32.380 --> 00:23:32.830 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Yeah.

00:23:32.830 --> 00:23:33.872 align:middle line:90%
STUDENT: --use your mass.

00:23:33.872 --> 00:23:34.660 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Right.

00:23:34.660 --> 00:23:37.000 align:middle line:84%
STUDENT: Without that being
comparable, how does that--

00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:37.300 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Yeah.

00:23:37.300 --> 00:23:38.038 align:middle line:84%
STUDENT: Because it's
not the same thing

00:23:38.038 --> 00:23:38.530 align:middle line:90%
as the relativistic--

00:23:38.530 --> 00:23:38.740 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Yeah.

00:23:38.740 --> 00:23:40.660 align:middle line:84%
There's not much you
