OK, good.

00:25:00.430 --> 00:25:09.610 align:middle line:84%
Just to summarize what
we have discussed so far,

00:25:09.610 --> 00:25:16.300 align:middle line:90%
all paths leads to QFT.

00:25:16.300 --> 00:25:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So we have described
three paths,

00:25:19.990 --> 00:25:21.550 align:middle line:90%
but they are pretty general.

00:25:21.550 --> 00:25:23.930 align:middle line:84%
First is that the
quantum dynamics--

00:25:23.930 --> 00:25:30.200 align:middle line:84%
we often interested
in quantum dynamics

00:25:30.200 --> 00:25:39.630 align:middle line:84%
of some classical fields,
say, such as, say,

00:25:39.630 --> 00:25:43.350 align:middle line:84%
electric magnetic field
or spacetime metric

00:25:43.350 --> 00:25:50.440 align:middle line:84%
if you are interested
in gravity, et cetera.

00:25:50.440 --> 00:25:54.950 align:middle line:84%
So in this case, we already
have the classical field theory,

00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:56.740 align:middle line:84%
but we know the world
is quantum and we

00:25:56.740 --> 00:25:59.510 align:middle line:84%
want to understand what's
the quantum version of it.

00:25:59.510 --> 00:26:05.680 align:middle line:84%
And the second is that it
unifies special relativity

00:26:05.680 --> 00:26:07.930 align:middle line:90%
plus quantum mechanics.

00:26:07.930 --> 00:26:10.820 align:middle line:84%
So you need the field
theory to unify them.

00:26:10.820 --> 00:26:25.220 align:middle line:84%
And the third way is that it's
the large distance description

00:26:25.220 --> 00:26:26.490 align:middle line:90%
of these grid systems.

00:26:26.490 --> 00:26:33.840 align:middle line:90%


00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:34.650 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:26:34.650 --> 00:26:40.190 align:middle line:84%
