00:40:08.360 --> 00:40:12.280 align:middle line:90%


00:40:12.280 --> 00:40:16.160 align:middle line:84%
So this is the form
we will often use.

00:40:16.160 --> 00:40:18.740 align:middle line:84%
You can also use that
form, but the equivalent,

00:40:18.740 --> 00:40:22.520 align:middle line:84%
but this is the form
we will often use.

00:40:22.520 --> 00:40:24.600 align:middle line:84%
You can also, from here,
you take the derivative,

00:40:24.600 --> 00:40:26.543 align:middle line:84%
you can find the P.
So again, this will

00:40:26.543 --> 00:40:27.710 align:middle line:90%
become an operator equation.

00:40:27.710 --> 00:40:29.283 align:middle line:84%
You take the
derivative of x hat--

00:40:29.283 --> 00:40:32.630 align:middle line:84%
x, and then you
find p, et cetera.

00:40:32.630 --> 00:40:36.150 align:middle line:90%


00:40:36.150 --> 00:40:36.650 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:40:36.650 --> 00:40:42.767 align:middle line:84%
So you-- p hat t, you
just take the derivative.

00:40:42.767 --> 00:40:46.260 align:middle line:90%


00:40:46.260 --> 00:40:48.410 align:middle line:90%
Then you can just work it out.

00:40:48.410 --> 00:40:49.035 align:middle line:90%
It's very easy.

00:40:49.035 --> 00:40:52.430 align:middle line:90%


00:40:52.430 --> 00:40:57.680 align:middle line:90%
So now-- so this equation just--

00:40:57.680 --> 00:41:00.200 align:middle line:84%
so we already solved
the quantum problem

00:41:00.200 --> 00:41:02.600 align:middle line:84%
because we find the full
evolution-- full solution

00:41:02.600 --> 00:41:05.900 align:middle line:84%
