Good?

00:49:41.270 --> 00:49:41.800 align:middle line:90%
OK, good.

00:49:41.800 --> 00:49:44.710 align:middle line:90%
So now it become a mechanical.

00:49:44.710 --> 00:49:50.380 align:middle line:84%
We can just apply
this to this theory.

00:49:50.380 --> 00:49:52.100 align:middle line:84%
We can just apply
this to this theory.

00:49:52.100 --> 00:49:53.960 align:middle line:90%
And now let me add here.

00:49:53.960 --> 00:49:58.495 align:middle line:84%
So here, the canonical momentum
density conjugate to phi is--

00:49:58.495 --> 00:50:02.720 align:middle line:84%
I called it pi before, is just
the time derivative of phi.

00:50:02.720 --> 00:50:07.090 align:middle line:84%
And the Hamiltonian density,
you can find it explicitly,

00:50:07.090 --> 00:50:10.380 align:middle line:90%
is pi squared plus 1/2.

00:50:10.380 --> 00:50:17.990 align:middle line:90%


00:50:17.990 --> 00:50:20.220 align:middle line:84%
And then this is the
classical equation of motion.

00:50:20.220 --> 00:50:20.720 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:50:20.720 --> 00:50:23.860 align:middle line:90%


00:50:23.860 --> 00:50:26.320 align:middle line:84%
So we can-- now let's just
solve this classical equation

00:50:26.320 --> 00:50:26.820 align:middle line:90%
of motion.

00:50:26.820 --> 00:50:29.320 align:middle line:90%


00:50:29.320 --> 00:50:32.070 align:middle line:90%
So this equation can be--

00:50:32.070 --> 00:50:35.100 align:middle line:84%
so this equation is
easy to solve because

00:50:35.100 --> 00:50:38.730 align:middle line:90%
of the translation symmetry.

00:50:38.730 --> 00:50:41.130 align:middle line:84%
You can just do a
Fourier transform.

00:50:41.130 --> 00:50:45.130 align:middle line:90%
So we can Fourier transform.

00:50:45.130 --> 00:50:47.655 align:middle line:90%
So now let's do can--

00:50:47.655 --> 00:50:50.320 align:middle line:90%
you can Fourier transform.

00:50:50.320 --> 00:50:56.810 align:middle line:90%
So 2 prime can be solved using--

00:50:56.810 --> 00:51:04.430 align:middle line:90%


00:51:04.430 --> 00:51:06.020 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:51:06.020 --> 00:51:11.900 align:middle line:84%
So we can just write phi
x equal to exponential

00:51:11.900 --> 00:51:16.730 align:middle line:90%
minus iEt plus i k dot x.

00:51:16.730 --> 00:51:24.260 align:middle line:90%


00:51:24.260 --> 00:51:26.270 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:51:26.270 --> 00:51:27.200 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:51:27.200 --> 00:51:32.180 align:middle line:84%
And then you can see then
this just solves the--

00:51:32.180 --> 00:51:48.260 align:middle line:84%
so this is provide a basis
of solutions to 2 prime.

00:51:48.260 --> 00:51:50.630 align:middle line:84%
It's just a plane wave,
just a plane wave.

00:51:50.630 --> 00:51:54.760 align:middle line:90%


00:51:54.760 --> 00:51:57.600 align:middle line:84%
So now when you plug
this into there,

00:51:57.600 --> 00:52:00.690 align:middle line:84%
then you just get the
dispersion relation.

00:52:00.690 --> 00:52:06.300 align:middle line:84%
Each square should be m
squared plus k squared.

00:52:06.300 --> 00:52:11.790 align:middle line:84%
So we'll denote this
as omega k squared.

00:52:11.790 --> 00:52:19.500 align:middle line:84%
So omega k is defined to be just
the k squared plus m squared.

00:52:19.500 --> 00:52:26.540 align:middle line:90%


00:52:26.540 --> 00:52:29.450 align:middle line:84%
So E-- when you take
the square root of E--

00:52:29.450 --> 00:52:32.810 align:middle line:84%
so you can take
plus-minus omega k.

00:52:32.810 --> 00:52:34.670 align:middle line:90%
Can we plus-minus omega k?

00:52:34.670 --> 00:52:39.010 align:middle line:84%
So we normally
call the solution--

00:52:39.010 --> 00:52:53.050 align:middle line:84%
we normally separate-- so
for historical reasons,

00:52:53.050 --> 00:52:55.030 align:middle line:90%
we normally put--

00:52:55.030 --> 00:53:02.110 align:middle line:84%
define u k x to be exponential
minus i omega k t--

00:53:02.110 --> 00:53:06.530 align:middle line:90%


00:53:06.530 --> 00:53:07.030 align:middle line:90%
x.

00:53:07.030 --> 00:53:11.930 align:middle line:84%
OK, now we have inserted
the positive root of E.

00:53:11.930 --> 00:53:15.875 align:middle line:84%
So this is normally called
the positive energy solution.

00:53:15.875 --> 00:53:20.710 align:middle line:90%


00:53:20.710 --> 00:53:26.560 align:middle line:84%
Even though this-- even though
this name is a little bit

00:53:26.560 --> 00:53:27.640 align:middle line:90%
misleading.

00:53:27.640 --> 00:53:33.490 align:middle line:84%
So actually, this-- we don't
define the energy actually--

00:53:33.490 --> 00:53:35.290 align:middle line:84%
yeah, later we will
see, this is not really

00:53:35.290 --> 00:53:38.710 align:middle line:90%
the energy of a particle.

00:53:38.710 --> 00:53:41.410 align:middle line:84%
And so this is just
a traditional name.

00:53:41.410 --> 00:53:43.210 align:middle line:90%
This is just a traditional name.

00:53:43.210 --> 00:53:44.650 align:middle line:90%
Conventional name.

00:53:44.650 --> 00:53:48.960 align:middle line:84%
And then you can define
the complex conjugate of k.

00:53:48.960 --> 00:53:51.010 align:middle line:90%
And now you have--

00:53:51.010 --> 00:53:57.035 align:middle line:84%
then corresponding, you have
a minus omega k in there.

00:53:57.035 --> 00:54:00.780 align:middle line:90%


00:54:00.780 --> 00:54:06.140 align:middle line:84%
So we take this
complex conjugate.

00:54:06.140 --> 00:54:08.265 align:middle line:84%
And so this is called the
negative energy solution.

00:54:08.265 --> 00:54:13.350 align:middle line:90%


00:54:13.350 --> 00:54:19.530 align:middle line:84%
So altogether, they form a
complete set of solutions.

00:54:19.530 --> 00:54:21.270 align:middle line:90%
So complete set of solutions.

00:54:21.270 --> 00:54:26.150 align:middle line:90%


00:54:26.150 --> 00:54:29.740 align:middle line:84%
So complete basis--
it's a complete set of--

00:54:29.740 --> 00:54:45.678 align:middle line:84%
complete basis is formed by u
k and the u k star for all k.

00:54:45.678 --> 00:54:48.860 align:middle line:90%


00:54:48.860 --> 00:54:50.590 align:middle line:90%
For all k.

00:54:50.590 --> 00:54:52.330 align:middle line:90%
So these are-- when you--

00:54:52.330 --> 00:54:54.370 align:middle line:84%
these are the complete
set of solutions

00:54:54.370 --> 00:54:55.900 align:middle line:90%
to that wave equation.

00:54:55.900 --> 00:54:58.420 align:middle line:90%
So that's just the--

